<TITLE> JP Ctg mayoral candidate warned </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May24 (bdnews24.com)  The Election Commission in a letter warned Jatiya Party's Chittagong mayoral candidate for putting up coloured posters prior to the formal election campaign. EC issued the letter Monday afternoon as coloured posters with photographs of Jatiya party city convenor Solayman Sheth appeared on the walls of the port city, ahead of the June 17 city corporation election. The letter undersigned by returning officer and deputy secretary of the EC Jasmine Tuli asked for immediate removal of the posters and informing the authority within 48 hours. Assistant returning officer and district election officer Farhad Hossain told bdnews24.com: "Coloured posters with photos of mayoral candidate Solaiman Sheth were seen in the city's Tiger Pass to Station Road area." "It is a violation of the electoral law." He said the letter asked for submitting a report to the returning officer by within hours after taking off the posters. Meanwhile, mayoral candidate M A Salam appealed after his nomination was primarily declared invalid. On top of that, nine ward councillor candidates and two reserved ward councillor candidates appealed to the divisional commissioner for reconsidering their candidature. bd
